results.occurrenceRemarks: Saw several of these wasps while walking along the walking-track. Not too easy to approach as they were constantly on the move, but lucky to find this one busily attending to its prey (looks like a nursery-web spider).

results.occurrenceRemarks: This fellow flew out of my compost tumbler so initially I assumed that it was a soldier fly adult.  I have abundant larvae in the tumbler.  However, I noticed that the abdomen is longer than the wings for this insect, whereas the soldier fly has longer wings than the abdomen.  I think it is a spider wasp.
